Two people died yesterday and three were injured in an accident on Lagos-Sagamu Expressway. A Golf car, marked FKJ 764 XB, a mini-truck, registered as ABG 352 ZD and an unmarked bus carrying musical equipment were involved in the crash. It occurred when the bus ran into the truck in a bid to avoid colliding with the car. The driver of the bus and a passenger died. Spokesman for the Ogun State Traffic Compliance and Enforcement Corps (TRACE), Babatunde Akinbiyi, who confirmed the accident, attributed it to careless driving. He said the injured were taken to Idera Hospital, Ajaka, Sagamu, and the bodies kept at Fakoya Hospital, also in Sagamu. 